In this speech, the speaker, who is representing President Joe Biden, addresses the issue of homelessness in America. They acknowledge the progress that has been made in addressing homelessness, but also highlight the ongoing challenges. The speaker discusses the efforts made by the Biden-Harris Administration to address homelessness, including the distribution of emergency housing vouchers and the investment in permanent, safe, supportive housing. They also mention the distribution of rental assistance to prevent evictions and the coordination of efforts between different government agencies. The speaker emphasizes the need to address homelessness from an equity perspective, focusing on communities that are disproportionately affected. They also highlight the importance of addressing mental health and substance use issues, as well as the need to decriminalize homelessness. The speaker concludes by calling for continued collaboration and investment to end homelessness and ensure that everyone has a safe and affordable home.